<Content>Perfect Location We stayed at Hotel Miramar in Kowloon for 3 nights. The hotel was having the lobby refurbished which made it a bit hard to find the entrance, but once we did we were greeted by friendly helpful staff. The staff were always courteous and helpful throughout our stay.We booked the executive club which allowed us many privileges. (Executive club foodspread is always basic in HK compared to other countries).Our room was had 1980's decor, but it was perfectly clean and spacious. The hotel was located centrally. The central shopping mall and the star ferry pier were within walking distance, as was the MTR which is essential in HK. It was easy for us to come back and drop shopping off and venture out again because of it's location. There were nearby night markets and Ashley Road closeby has some great bars and restaurants. Nearby Chung Kung Mall offers the best exchange rates.We stayed at the Exelsior a couple of years ago - Miramar is definately better.I am sure this hotel will have an amazing lobby next year, especially if the temporary one is anything to go by!This is an ideal city hotel and I do not have any reservations recommending it. 
