<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>Struck it lucky Other reviewers seem to have a love/hate experience; we got just what we were hoping for.We were overnighting on our way across the world and just needed enough room and quiet for my wife, 2-year- and 6-month-old and myself to catch up on sleep and have a base from which to explore a little. We only booked about two days ahead through an online agency, and the requested extra bed for our toddler had not been confirmed. It wasn't there when we got into our room but, seeing how big the beds were (they were what I would call a 3/4 bed - certainly big enough for two people), we didn't care. If I were staying for longer and weren't planning on sleeping most of the time I would make sure to get a room not facing the interior courtyard, which is basically three huge boilers and some roofing - very stagnant chi. I suspect the room used to be smoking-allowed, because it couldn't quite shake a dank musty smell - or is that Hong Kong in general?The staff were helpful, and not being hotel users normally we were thrilled at having people handle our luggage and hail taxis for us, although tipping is a mystery to New Zealanders (for the record: the front desk lady recommended HK$20 for porters, which seemed to do the trick).We didn't make use of the hotel facilities apart from their broadband, but I must say being across the road from Kowloon Park is great, and it's in the middle of a whole heap of shops. There are good and varied eateries in the Miramar Mall across the street. So I would certainly stay here again. A note on airport transfers: I generally like to use public transport, but we took a taxi each way at non-peak times, which cost just shy of $300 each time - better than saving a few dollars if you are struggling with kids and luggage. 
