<Content>Great location but rooms need updating I have stayed in many hotels in Hong Kong I would say that if you are going to stay in Kowloon this has the best location. It is right by the MTR, buses, shops, good restaurants etc and is in a bustling part of town. I would recommend the chinese restaurant in the hotel at which we ate a delicious and very reasonable lunch on two occasions. The cafe/buffet on the ground floor was also good. I used the pool and gym which were satisfactory and as a guest was surprised to be charged a small fee for this.The rooms are bigger than most in HK and ours was clean, though quite tired looking and in need of a facelift. I learned after my stay that the hotel is in two parts, the old (which we were in) and newly built part, and that the rooms are nicer in the new one but smaller. We did have problems with the air con system leaking which affected several rooms on our floor but was promptly seen to and cleaned up. The main problem we had was noise. We stayed on the 5th floor and every night could hear the hotels bar/disco playing thumping music till at least 1am (sunday i think) and 2-3 am every other night. I would stay here again for the location and convenience only if I got another good deal on the rates. I would also stay in the new part and ask to be higher up to avoid any noise. 
