<Content>Great Location, OK Service, Run Down Rooms Stayed for 6 days in Jun 2005 for the third time. Don't let the lobby fool you. The rooms are not as impressive as the lobby.When we checked in, they informed us that the only rooms available were non-smoking rooms without a window or smoking rooms. When we told them both were unacceptable, they told us that our travel agency did not request either. So, they could put us in whichever room available. After more arguing, they told us we would have to wait 40 minutes for a nonsmoking room with a window. Until then, I had not realized a window had to be requested! The concierge desk was very accomodating and friendly.The furniture was run down and the bathroom tile was a bit scary: the grout was moldy and disgusting. The carpet was run down, but somewhat clean. The towels were okay, but reminds me of towels from a two star hotel. The rooms were spacious. The room we stayed in had advertisements indicating that the room had broadband access. When we inquired about broadband access, the front desk informed us that it was not available for the standard room. Why advertise it if it isn't available?The hotel is in a very good location. We weren't too far in Tsimshatsui where we would have to take a subway/taxi to get to other parts of Kowloon. This is not what I expected for a 4 star hotel. I expected a more accomomadting front desk and a less run down room. I will most likely not stay at the Miramar again. 
